	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'green-bell-pepper' %}<div id="green-bell-pepper" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-green-bell-pepper.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Green Bell Pepper" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Green Bell Pepper<br><i>Capsicum Annuum Group</i></h4><p>Green bell peppers are the unripened version of their colorful red and orange counterparts. 1 cup of these peppers can provide around 10% of your daily fiber intake and 125% of your daily recommended vitamin C intake - but don't worry, a little extra doesn't hurt!</p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'green-coffee-bean' %}<div id="green-coffee-bean" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-green-coffee-bean.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Green Coffee Bean" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Green Coffee Bean<br><i>Coffea Arabica</i></h4><p>Most of us know coffee to be a great source of energy due to being high in caffeine, however, these unroasted beans also contain chlorogenic acid which has been studied for its ability to aid in weight loss. [1] </p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'leek' %}<div id="leek" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-leek.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Leek" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Leek<br><i>Allium Ampeloprasum</i></h4><p>A 100 gram serving of leeks contains around 2 grams of dietary fiber and a gram of protein. These lovely greens are also a great source of vitamins A and K, folic acid, niacin, riboflavin, magnesium, and thiamin.</p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'maca-root' %}<div id="maca-root" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-maca-root.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Maca Root" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Maca Root<br><i>Lepidium Meyenii</i></h4><p>There's a reason why people often say consuming maca makes them feel more “alive”! This Peruvian root has been shown to support endurance and even used to support learning abilities and cognitive function.<sup><a target="_blank" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21977053/">[1]</a></sup></p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'oat-grass' %}<div id="oat-grass" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-oat-grass.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Oat Grass Powder" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Oat Grass Powder<br><i>Arrhenatherum Elatius</i></h4><p>Oat grass joins wheatgrass and barley grass as part of the cereal grass family. Rich in chlorophyll, beta-carotene, vitamins K and C, folic acid, calcium, iron, protein, fiber, and B vitamins, extracts of Oat Grass could even improve cognitive performance, according to a study published in the Journal of Alternative and Complementary Medicine.<sup><a target="_blank" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21711204">[1]</a></sup></p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'pomegranate' %}<div id="pomegranate" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-pomegranate.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Pomegranate" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Pomegranate<br><i>Rubus Idaeus L.</i></h4><p>A great source of Vitamins C and K, pomegranate is a fibrous berry that is also super-high in antioxidants, showing antioxidant activity <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11052704" target="_blank" alt="pomegranate antioxidant">three times higher</a> than that of green tea. Yum!</p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'rhodiola-root' %}<div id="rhodiola-root" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-rhodiola-root.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Rhodiola Root" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Rhodiola Root<br><i>Rhodiola Rosea</i></h4><p>There's a reason why this versatile adaptogen herb is used by athletes all over the world as a natural energy enhancer.<sup><a target="_blank" href="http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1541-4337.2005.tb00073.x/abstract">[1]</a></sup> Studies have shown Rhodiola to support cognitive function such as concentration and memory.<sup><a target="_blank" href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S094471131000036X">[2]</a></sup></p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'sea-kelp' %}<div id="sea-kelp" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-sea-kelp.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Sea Kelp" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Sea Kelp<br><i>Macrocystis Pyrifera</i></h4><p>Kelp is a type of large seaweed that are famous for growing from the sea floor to the surface, seeking sunlight and can grow at amazingly fast rates, sometimes more than half a meter a day! This fast-growing superfood has amino acids that make it nearly a complete protein.<sup><a target="_blank" href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0924224499000151">[1]</a></sup></p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'stevia' %}<div id="stevia" class="ingredient"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-stevia.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Stevia Leaf" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Stevia Leaf<br><i>Stevia rebaudiana</i></h4><p>Stevia rebaudiana has been used for more than 1,500 years by the Guaraní peoples of South America. <sup><a target="_blank" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3103919">[1]</a></sup> Known as the "sweet herb", it provides sweetness without the caloric intake normally associated with sugar. We only use trace amounts in our products to bring out the sweetness of other ingredients, rather than trying to build flavors around the distinct stevia taste.</p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'sunflower-lecithin' %}<div id="sunflower-lecithin" class="ingredient"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-sunflower-lecithin.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Sunflower Lecithin" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Sunflower Lecithin<br><i>Helianthus</i></h4><p>Lecithin is a type of phospholipid found in pure sunflower seeds. It's a natural source of phosphatidylcholine, a natural constituent found in your brain and nervous system.</p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'tapioca' %}<div id="tapioca" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-tapioca.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Tapioca" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Tapioca<br><i>Manihot Esculenta</i></h4><p>Tapioca is a starch extracted from the Cassava root, native to South America. It is used in a wide array of South American and Asian cooking, but it is also a good prebiotic, being naturally high in dietary fiber.</p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'triphala' %}<div id="triphala" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-triphala.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Triphala" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Triphala<br><i>Myrobalans</i></h4><p>Literally meaning 'three fruits' this Ayurvedic herbal formula consists of equal parts of three myrobalans: Amalaki, Bibhitaki, and Haritaki. Triphala has been shown to have powerful antioxidant effects, protecting cells from the damage of free radicals.<sup><a target="_blank" href="http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/ptr.1515/abstract">[1]</a></sup> Studies also show that this herbal formulation not only supports the GI system,<sup><a target="_blank" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25756303">[2]</a></sup> but also promotes a healthy immune and cardiovascular system.<sup><a target="_blank" href="http://www.bioline.org.br/pdf?pt06008">[3]</a></sup></p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'turmeric' %}<div id="turmeric" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-turmeric.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Turmeric" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Turmeric<br><i>Curcuma Longa</i></h4><p>Turmeric has long been used in Ayurvedic medicine in South Asia and is plentiful in antioxidants. <span class="clickbank-hide">Preliminary studies on curcuminoids found in turmeric have been found to potentially reduce the number of heart attacks bypass patients had after surgery<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22481014" target="_blank">[1]</a>, support control of knee pain from osteoarthritis as well as ibuprofen did <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19678780" target="_blank">[2]</a> and reduce skin irritation <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23745991" target="_blank">[3]</a>.</span></p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'wheat-grass' %}<div id="wheat-grass" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-wheat-grass.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Wheat Grass Juice Powder" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Wheat Grass Juice Powder<br><i>Triticum Aestivum</i></h4><p>Wheat Grass is often synonymous with the term 'superfood'! This green beauty has been known to increase red blood cell count to help boost immune system function<sup><a target="_blank" href="http://www.chemijournal.com/vol2issue4/dec2014/2-3-9.1.pdf">[1]</a></sup> and it's b-complex vitamins are great for aiding digestion.</p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'yerba-mate' %}<div id="yerba-mate" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-yerba-mate.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Yerba Mate" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Yerba Mate<br><i>Ilex Paraguariensis</i></h4><p>The herb Yerba Mate contains the stimulating compounds theobromine and caffeine, known to increase energy levels as well as improve focus<sup><a target="_blank" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1356551">[1]</a></sup> without the jittery side effects. Caffeine has also been shown to improve muscle contractions, reduce fatigue and improve sports performance by up to 5%.<sup><a target="_blank" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20492310">[2]</a></sup> One study showed men and women given one 1-gram capsule of yerba mate right before moderate-intensity exercise burned 24% more fat than those who weren't given Yerba Mate.<sup><a target="_blank" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4190939/">[3]</a></sup></p></div></div>{% endif %}

	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'lactobacillus-rhamnosus-gg' %}<div id="lactobacillus-rhamnosus-gg" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'probiotic-lactobacillus-rhamnosus-gg.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="Lactobacillus Rhamnosus GG" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Lactobacillus Rhamnosus GG<br><i>Probiotic Strain</i></h4><p>Lactobacillus Rhamnosus GG is the most widely studied probiotic strain with proven benefits on supporting the immune system. In one study children who were given the strain vs those who were given a placebo had a significantly reduced risk of upper respiratory tract infections, a reduced risk of respiratory tract infections lasting longer than 3 days, and a significantly lower number of days with respiratory symptoms.<sup><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19896252" target="_blank">[1]</a></sup></p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'lactobacillus-paracasei' %}<div id="lactobacillus-paracasei" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'probiotic-lactobacillus-paracasei.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="Lactobacillus Paracasei" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Lactobacillus Paracasei<br><i>Probiotic Strain</i></h4><p>Lactobacillus Paracasei is a great probiotic for adults and children alike, helping to support a healthy immune system and digestion. A study of 379 children published in 2014 found that children provided with this probiotic strain were less susceptible to digestive issues or fever.<sup><a href="http://www.journalrepository.org/media/journals/EJNFS_30/2014/May/Hemalatha442013EJNFS8280_1.pdf" target="_blank">[1]</a></sup></p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'rice-concentrate' %}<div id="rice-concentrate" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-rice-concentrate.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Rice Concentrate" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Rice Concentrate<br><i>Rice Hulls</i></h4><p>Organic Rice Concentrate is a powder made from the finely milled and ground hulls of rice. This stops powder products from caking, keeping them smooth and easy to mix, without having to use synthetic alternatives like silicon dioxide.</p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'gum-acacia' %}<div id="gum-acacia" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-gum-acacia.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Gum Acacia" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Gum Acacia<br><i>Acacia Nilotica</i></h4><p>This is a natural gum consisting of the hardened sap of various species of the acacia tree. Not only does this gum act as a carrier for organic flavors, but it's also a good source of fiber. It's also been used for centuries in traditional arabic medicine to heal wounds, hence its alternative name, arabic gum.</p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'mango-pineapple-natural-flavors' %}<div id="mango-flavor" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-mango-flavor.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Mango Flavor" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Mango Flavor<br><i>Mangifera Indica</i></h4><p>This product contains the delicious organic-compliant flavor of mango! Organic compliant means that this flavor was created using organic certified methods. Learn more about the different types of nautral flavors <a href="https://www.ora.organic/blogs/news/what-are-natural-flavors" target="_blank">here</a>.</p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'organic-echninacea' %}<div id="organic-echninacea" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-organic-echninacea.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Echinacea" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Echinacea<br><i>Echinacea Purpurea</i></h4><p>Echinacea (A.K.A. purple coneflower) is a North American species of flower in the sunflower family that is used in traditional Native American medicine as well as pharmaceuticals. One study showed echinacea had a beneficial effect on adults with cold symptoms in clinical trials, especially in comparison to placebo, if treatment is begun early.<sup><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10228604" target="_blank" alt="echinacea study">[1]</sup></a></p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'guar' %}<div id="guar" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-guar.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Organic Guar Gum" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Organic Guar Gum<br><i>Cyamopsis tetragonoloba</i></h4><p>Guar gum is a dietary fiber derived from the pods of the Indian cluster bean Guar. Guar is native to the tropical Asian climate, but has been grown int he souther US since the beginning of the 20th century.<sup><a href="https://www.drugs.com/npp/guar-gum.html#ref1" target="blank">[1]</sup></a> It is most often used as a thickening agent in food and nutritional products, helping to stop chalkiness in plant-based powders and improve the texture of your smoothies.</p></div></div>{% endif %}
	{% if ingredient_handle contains 'mango-pineapple-natural-flavors' %}<div id="pineapple-flavor" class="ingredient {{ ingredient_flavor }}"><img src="{{ 'ingredients-pineapple-flavor.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Pineapple Flavor" rel="share"/><div class="description"><h4>Pineapple Flavor<br><i>Ananas comosus</i></h4><p>This product contains the delicious organic-compliant flavor of pineapple! Organic compliant means that this flavor was created using organic certified methods. Learn more about the different types of nautral flavors <a href="https://www.ora.organic/blogs/news/what-are-natural-flavors" target="_blank">here</a>.</p></div></div>{% endif %}

{% endfor %}
